title: "2001: A Space Odyssey"
rating: 0.1
review {
  direction {
    director {
      name: "Stanley Kubrick"
    }
    rating: "TODO"
    comments: "The direction on a macroscale is grand and groundbreaking as Kubrick uses his signature style to push the limits what can be seen on the big screen; the direction on a microscale has a lot of the signature Kubrick charm and style, but feels a little to slow and dragged out;  the storytelling is very non-traditional as it really tells 3 differnt stories (resembling an 'Odyssey' across space), but this non-traditional style does take away from the enjoyability aspect because the narrative they do have, is pretty dry; he builds tension incredibly well the movie definitely is a gradual build in tension and anxiety as the movie goes on"
  }
