  story {
    writer {
      name: "Stanley Kubrick"
    }
    writer {
      name: "Arthur C. Clarke"
    }
    rating: "Good"
    comments: "The concept is great as the movie is an odyessy across space to explore what is beyond humanity, while simulatinously showing the flaws of humanity; the plot structure is non-traditional as the movie is treated more like an odyessy with multiple archs, but this is a double edged-sword as it makes you less invested in the stories and characters because of it; character writing is alright, but the only really interesting character is HAL as the rest are really just typical astronauts"
  }
  screenplay {
    writer {
      name: "Stanley Kubrick"
    }
    writer {
      name: "Arthur C. Clarke"
    }
    rating: "Good"
    comments: "The dialogue is pretty standard for Kubrick and movies from the time period, but does include many iconic lines (especially from HAL); the humor is unintential, but does hit; the symbolism is quite profound as it touches aspects of humanity, AI, science-fiction, and evolution; the foreshadowing is carried out very well (especially as the movie transitions into the final arc)"
  }
  soundtrack {
    rating: "Great"
    comments: "Uses a soundtreak instead of a score; helps really paint the scenes and make the movie iconic"
  }
  cinematography {
    cinematographer {
      name: "Geoffrey Unsworth"
    }
    rating: "Brilliant"
    comments: "Helps make the movie visually stunning; Groundbreaking for the time, with its lighting and angles; Incredibly Kubrick"
  }
  editing {
    editor {
      name: "Ray Lovejoy"
    }
    rating: "Decent"
    comments: "While the movie does feel professionally cut, there are some edits that I felt really lacked continuity; The movies cut felt a little too elongated as there were many shots and moments that could have been cut (especially in the first half)"
  }
  sound {
    rating: "Great"
    comments: "Incredibly deafening as it helps paint the world and the scenes and provides tension"
  }
  visual_effects {
    rating: "Brilliant"
    comments: "Groundbreaking for the time as it pushes the bounds of cinema and technology to create an influential artpiece; helps make the movie visually stunning"
  }
  production_design {
    rating: "Incredible"
    comments: "Feels very groundbreaking; very Kubrick"
  }
  costumes {
    rating: "Good"
    comments: "Helps capture the setting"
  }
  pacing: "Pacing is incredibly slow as it includes so much filler that hurts the enjoyability of this movie; the first half could hav ebeen cut in half and it would've been the same film"
  climax: "Climax is executed well as it is very tense; the exposition feels a little too long, but is still visually stunning"
  tone: "Tone is a science-fiction odyseey, mixed with some thriller elements"
  final_notes: "The movie is a little too Avant-Guard (which takes away from it being enjoyable);"
  overall: "Overall, an influential film as Kubrick pushes both the bounds of cinema and tehcnology to create a groundbreaking space odyseey, but the incredibly slow pacing, non-traditional narrative style, and filler really hurt how enjoyable this movie can be"
